   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Fire Scorpion Charm</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img title="Fire Scorpion Charm" src="/file/Elden-Ring/fire_scorpion_charm_talisman_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="fire scorpion charm talisman elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Weight</td> 
     <td>0.8</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <img style="width: 22px; height: 22px;" title="status_effect_83_elden_ring_wiki_guide_44px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/status_effect_83_elden_ring_wiki_guide_44px.png" alt="status effect 83 elden ring wiki guide 44px" width="22" height="22">Increases 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fire Damage" href="/Fire+Damage" target="">Fire Damage</a>&nbsp;by 12%, but increases&nbsp; 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Physical Damage" href="/Physical+Damage" target="">Physical Damage</a>&nbsp;taken by 10% 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Fire Scorpion Charm</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Talismans" href="/Talismans">Talisman</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Fire Scorpion Charm</strong> increases <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fire Damage" href="/Fire+Damage" target="">Fire Damage</a>&nbsp;by 12%, but increases&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Physical Damage" href="/Physical+Damage" target="">Physical Damage</a>&nbsp;taken by 10%. Players can use <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Talismans" href="/Talismans" target="">Talismans</a>&nbsp;in Elden Ring to boost a variety of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stats" href="/Stats" target="">Stats</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen.<br>Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that burns with fire.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Raises fire attack power, but lowers damage negation.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Fire Scorpion Charm Effect in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p><strong>Fire Scorpion Charm</strong>&nbsp;increases <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fire Damage" href="/Fire+Damage" target="">Fire Damage</a>&nbsp;by 12%, but increases&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Physical Damage" href="/Physical+Damage" target="">Physical Damage</a>&nbsp;taken by 10%.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Increases Fire Damage by 8% in PvP.</li> 
 <li>Increases Physical Damage taken by 15% in PvP.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Fire Scorpion Charm in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Fire Scorpion Charm</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Found up the ramparts on a wooden platform to the west in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fort Laiedd" href="/Fort+Laiedd">Fort Laiedd</a> within <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mt Gelmir" href="/Mt+Gelmir">Mt. Gelmir</a>.&nbsp;[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1340&amp;lat=-85.882812&amp;lng=56.79324&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1340&amp;lat=-85.882812&amp;lng=56.79324&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Fire Scorpion Charm Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Buff stacks multiplicatively with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Flame-Shrouding Cracked Tear" href="/Flame-Shrouding+Cracked+Tear">Flame-Shrouding Cracked Tear</a></li> 
 <li>Other notes &amp; tips go here.</li> 
</ul> 
